\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {1}{\ignorespaces Adaptive vs Fixed-Question Baseline Comparison on Real Models. The adaptive system achieves 50\% accuracy with 30\% fewer questions (5.6 vs 8.0 average). Both systems show 60\% lying detection, but adaptive improves truth detection from 20\% to 40\%.}}{10}{figure.caption.33}%
\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {2}{\ignorespaces Question Type Effectiveness Analysis. Detail probes dominate the question distribution (67\% of all questions, 38/57 total) and show highest effectiveness with +16.6\% average confidence change. Knowledge tests show similar effectiveness (+17.8\%) but with small sample size (2 questions).}}{11}{figure.caption.38}%
